        <name>XAsu_HmacSha3Kat</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function runs the client-side HMAC KAT using SHA3-256. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>    It calls XAsu_HmacCompute with INIT|UPDATE|FINAL, busy-waits for the callback,
    and compares the output against the expected HMAC.
</verbatim></para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if HMAC SHA3-256 KAT passes.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if HMAC computation or comparison fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Set up client parameters with KAT callback.</para><para>Set up HMAC parameters for single-shot operation.</para><para>Send HMAC compute request to the server.</para><para>Busy-wait for the server response.</para><para>Check the callback status.</para><para>Compare the computed HMAC against the expected value.</para><para>Zeroize local output buffer. </para>        </inbodydescription>
